[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This right here is the space agent, and it\'s unlike any other agent you have ever seen. It can completely change the way you work with AI agents. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; My name is Jan. I am the developer of Agent Zero, and today I\'m here to present our newest project made by Agent'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Zero, the space agent. In this video, I will show you what space agent actually is and what it can do, how it operates internally, and also why is it the fastest and most efficient agent out there. [music] Let\'s start with the'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'important part. Space agent, just like Agent Zero, is completely free and open source. You can use it for whatever you want. You can change it into whatever you want. It\'s up to you. Now, what makes space agent really different is this part right here. The agent lives'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in the front end. So, the agent runs in a browser, but [music] I don\'t mean it has a web UI like the other agent and the agent runs on a back end somewhere. This agent actually lives and executes inside the browser\'s'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'JavaScript runtime. All of the framework, everything you see, everything the agent can do, actually executes client-side in the front end layer in JavaScript. This comes with some security and privacy benefits. For'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'example, even the inference can be done in the browser using WebGPU, but the main reason &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; to do it this way is this, the spaces. Spaces are a way to let the agent modify'

[01:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the runtime environment as it needs to. If the agent needs to show you something, it can simply draw it on screen because the agent lives and operates in the front end layer. So, if you want a crypto dashboard with'

[01:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ticker prices, charts, and news, &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; the agent can draw it for you on the screen in real time. Or maybe a daily news overview with a list of news.'

[01:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; You can choose different sources. You see the top news of the day and weather dashboard. Even games [music] can be created by the agent from scratch in the browser in real time. The way spaces work is that the agent writes a renderer function for'

[02:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'individual widgets [music] once, and this function can then be used to recreate the widget anytime on this infinite grid. Meaning even if I refresh the page, my widgets stay in place in the same'

[02:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'shape they were before, and I\'m not losing any changes made to the DOM. Here, for example, we have YouTube player with a playlist of Agent Zero videos.'

